claim.claim-text:
1. A reactor system comprising:
a flexible bag having an interior surface bounding a compartment;
an elongated tubular connector disposed within the compartment of the flexible bag, the tubular connector having a first end and an opposing second end;
a rotational assembly which includes a casing mounted to the flexible bag and a hub rotatably mounted to the casing, the hub having a passageway extending therethrough, the first end of the tubular connector being secured to the hub;
an impeller disposed within the compartment of the flexible bag, the impeller being coupled with the second end of the tubular connector; and
a drive shaft removably received within the tubular connector and removably coupled with the impeller such that continuous rotation of the drive shaft facilitates continuous rotation of the impeller.

11. A method for mixing a fluid, the method comprising:
delivering a fluid into a compartment of a flexible bag, an elongated tubular connector being coupled to the flexible bag and projecting into the compartment thereof, an impeller being coupled with the tubular connector and disposed within the compartment;
removably inserting a drive shaft into the tubular connector so that the drive shaft engages with the impeller;
continuously rotating the drive shaft so that the drive shaft continuously rotates the impeller and mixes the fluid within the compartment; and
further comprising a casing mounted to the flexible bag and a hub rotatably mounted to the casing, the hub being coupled to the tubular connector and having a passageway extending therethrough, the step of removably inserting the drive shaft comprising passing the drive shaft through the passageway of the hub.

18. The reactor system as recited in claim 1, further comprising:
a housing;
a motor mount disposed on the housing and having a passage extending therethrough;
a drive motor coupled with the motor mount for selectively rotating the motor mount relative to the housing, the drive shaft being engaged with the motor mount so that rotation of the motor mount by the drive motor facilitates continuous rotation of the drive shaft.
